The Vice President, Mike Pence, gave a speech at the 100th National Convention of the American Legion in Minneapolis, Minnesota. He thanked the veterans for their service and acknowledged their sacrifice. Pence also honored the late Senator John McCain, who was a strong advocate for the armed forces. He highlighted the work that the American Legion has done over the past century to support veterans and their families. Pence mentioned the actions taken by the Trump administration to improve veterans' benefits, healthcare, and employment opportunities. He also discussed the efforts to strengthen the military and address national security challenges. Pence concluded his speech by expressing gratitude to the American Legion and the armed forces for their service to the nation.